place.name: CAMERON
place.gazetteerText: Cameron.-- par., E. Fifeshire, on Cameron Water, 3½ miles SW. of St Andrews, 9325 ac., pop. 1003. (In 1887, John Bartholomew's Gazetteer of the British Isles)

place.name: CAMERON BRIDGE
place.gazetteerText: Cameron Bridge, vil. with ry. sta. and distillery, Markinch par., Fifeshire, on river Leven, 3½ miles NE. of Thornton Junction. See WINDYGATES AND CAMERON BRIDGE. (In 1887, John Bartholomew's Gazetteer of the British Isles)
